fields.physical_description:
Design: playing board covered with red paper with the playing surface having a map of the world, names of international cities pinpointed with orange dots; story cards are printed in a black and white mottled design on the reverse side.
No. illustrated: some
fields.title: newsdesk; made in england.  some components imported.  7-adult.  604-4565-02. £5.49

fields.name:
Type: letters and words, spelling
Subject: newspapers

fields.history_note: The game is played with dice which govern the movement of the players around the map and the stories they submit to the papers.
fields.production_note: milton bradley ltd, under berne & universal copyright convention
fields.historical_context_note:
No. of Players: any
Equipment required: playing board
telex machine
front pages from newspapers
story cards and counters
original box

Rules: playing board, map printed in light and dark blue with the names of the international cities in white and black; in the lower left corner are the copyright details and in the lower right the number 4565-XGB
telex machine is of yellow plastic moulded with a typewriter keyboard and a telephone dial; on the top are two black dials which operated the telex tape within the machine; tape is held on two spools rather like tyepwriter ribbon and is printed with `news' items.
newspaper front pages, printed with some text and some holes to be filled - The Guardian, dated Thursday November 27, 1975, The Daily Telegraph, dated Monday, January 19, 1976, The Daily Express, dated Friday, November 16, 1973
story cards entitled WRITE OFF, SPECIAL REPORTER, MISSION COMPLETE with the subjects ART, CRIME, DISASTER, ECONOMICS, LOCAL NEWS, NEWS-IN-BRIEF, SCIENCE, SPORT
